In pig latin all letters before the initial vowel are placed at the end of the
word for words that begin with a consonant sound. Then 'ay' is added to the
end.
+1:pig
When words begin with consonant clusters the whole sound is added to the end
of the word. And of course, it ends with an 'ay'.
+1:cheers
For words that begin with vowel sounds, one just adds "way" to the end.
+1:eat
Sentences are constructed as a series of words. It is important to put
commas and punctuation in the right place!
+6:Words are lonely, sentences are tiresome.
The tutorial is now complete, have fun playing Pig Latin!
